    <text>
        <div facs="#eSc_textblock_183da727">
            <lb />
            <hi rendition="#c">
                <hi rendition="#i">
                    <hi rendition="#u">
                        <seg xml:id="immortals" ana="#immortality" resp="#np" type="topic">
                            The Instrument of the Immortals
                        </seg>
                        <note type="editorial" ref="#immortals" resp="#np">
                            The slogan was originally invented by
                            <persName>Raymond Rubicam</persName> in 1919, who
                            referred to the long-lasting history of Steinway pianos
                            (Julian Watkins, *The 100 Greatest Advertisements 1852–1958*,
                            p. 45).
                            Nevertheless, the "immortality" theme is analysed 
                            here, since the slogan gets reinterpreted by its 
                            context.
                        </note>
                    </hi>
                </hi>
            </hi>
        </div>
        <div facs="#eSc_dummyblock_">
            <lb />
            <head>
                <name type="brand">
                    Steinway
                    <lb />Welte
                    <lb />Grand
                </name>
